The paper deals with the design of a data structure (distance oracle) for answering distance queries in planar graphs. This involves techniques from data structures (cs.DS), computational geometry (cs.CG), and graph algorithms (cs.DM). The paper also discusses trade-offs between time and space, which involves information theory (cs.IT) and numerical analysis (cs.NA).
